DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Leukocyte Result Outcome Integer::2 Decimal Place Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The 2 decimal place numeric laboratory value measured, assigned or computed related to the assessment of white blood cells in a specimen.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the result of a medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for white blood cells, a blood cell that does not contain hemoglobin and includes monocytes, basophils, lymphocytes, neutrophils, eosinophils, macrophages, and mast cells.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: White blood cells. These include granular leukocytes (BASOPHILS, EOSINOPHILS, and NEUTROPHILS) as well as non-granular leukocytes (LYMPHOCYTES and MONOCYTES).:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: Blood cells that are devoid of hemoglobin, capable of ameboid motion and phagocytosis, and act as the principal components of the immune system.
